	<item>
		<title>Visit from LA</title>
		<link>https://www.afu.se/afu2/?p=8863</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Clas Svahn]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sun, 29 Jun 2025 10:33:41 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.afu.se/afu2/?p=8863</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[On June 21st AFU-chairman Clas Svahn was visited by American TV producer Chris Sanders. Chris was very impressed by AFU and it’s holdings but at this time had only time to visit Svahn at his house in Järfälla where he was given a Power Point presentation of AFU and a long talk about the archive.https://csblogg.ufo.se/csblogg3/?p=92767]]></description>
		
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>Large donation from Canada</title>
		<link>https://www.afu.se/afu2/?p=8812</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Clas Svahn]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sun, 13 Feb 2022 12:05:54 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[New donations]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.afu.se/afu2/?p=8812</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[A large collection of Canadian files arrived to AFU a couple of days ago. Two pallets with UFO reports, books, magazines, newsletters, gadgets, recorded tapes collected over 30 years by several local ufologists saved by researchers Drew Williamson from the files of Tom Theofanous, Larry Fenwick (CUFORN), Bonnie Wheeler (Cambridge UFO Research Group), Hugh F. [&#8230;]]]></description>
		
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>Large donation from Canada on its way</title>
		<link>https://www.afu.se/afu2/?p=8783</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Clas Svahn]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 01 Dec 2021 21:56:31 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[New donations]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.afu.se/afu2/?p=8783</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Finally, the two pallets of UFO material are on their way from Toronto! I was almost starting to wonder if they would never be picked up but after a third change of local transport company came the message from the company AFU and I cooperate with in the US at 17.26 today (December 1st) – [&#8230;]]]></description>
		
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>Visiting Crazy Pictures’ recording of new UFO film</title>
		<link>https://www.afu.se/afu2/?p=8753</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Anders Liljegren]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 16 Nov 2021 19:42:24 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.afu.se/afu2/?p=8753</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[On November 3, seven members of the AFU board and staff visited Crazy Pictures in their Norrköping studios. Crazy Pictures, the young Swedish film collective, who had a world-wide success with their 2018-premiered action film “Den blomstertid nu kommer” (The time of blossom now approaches). The film portrays an imagined (but plausible) summer invasion of [&#8230;]]]></description>
		
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>2021 annual White Weekend sale from the AFU Shop</title>
		<link>https://www.afu.se/afu2/?p=8749</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Anders Liljegren]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 09 Nov 2021 14:14:07 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.afu.se/afu2/?p=8749</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Take the opportunity to acquire a full &#8220;Christmas box&#8221; of paranormal print items from the AFU Shop. We now have 5.000 registered items with lots of variations. Those variations include thousands of old paranormal and UFO magazine issues from all over the world.&#160; Download the flyer&#160;for the White Weekend 2021 sale &#8211; November 12 &#8211; [&#8230;]]]></description>
		
		
		
			</item>
